The paper proposes a novel framework for semi-supervised learning using graph convolutional networks. The main focus is on improving the utilization of unlabeled data, which is a common problem in semi-supervised learning. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses Mean Teacher, which is a popular model in semi-supervised learning, indicating that it could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also mentions using the proposed method for classification tasks, which suggests that it could belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) or Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Finally, the paper uses a mutual-promoting process to train the model, which could be related to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
